 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Climate Adaptation Solutions Strategist One Concern Menlo Park, CA Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description One Concern is a Menlo Park-based benevolent artificial intelligence company with a mission to save lives and livelihoods before, during and after disasters. Founded at Stanford University, One Concern enables insurers, corporations, cities and citizens to embrace a disaster-free future, through AI-enabled technology solutions. By combining data science and natural phenomena science we are pursuing a vision for planetary-scale resilience, where everyone lives in a safe, equitable, and sustainable world. 
One Concern is growing rapidly, and we are looking for passionate, motivated, and high reaching people to join our team. 
One Concernâ€™s Solutions Team is seeking an Climate Adaptation Solutions Strategist. This role requires specialized skills in climate risk, adaptation, and financing domains; and an ability to understand the customer needs and industry trends. Climate Adaptation Strategist will work with the customers and multidisciplinary teams in the US and Japan to develop the strategy and specifications for our solution for various customers. 
 Responsibilities - Get ready to think big, work smart, and shine bright! 
Develop strategy and specifications for evolving One Concernâ€™s products and solutions for climate risk adaptation and financing, targeted at enterprises, insurers, banks, asset managers, and cities. 
Work closely with various cross-functional teams at One Concern (Solutions, Data Science, Engineering, Product Management, and Business Development) to build innovative and practical solutions and product offerings. 
Drive innovation within One Concern to stay ahead of client needs and to differentiate our offerings in the market. Help One Concern evolve its current value proposition for climate adaptation with our next key target clients across sectors by being active in the market, listening to clients, developing new service offerings and delivering high quality and impactful solutions to our clients. 
Keep up-to-date on the latest climate risk adaptation, climate resilience investments, risk financing market trends, and public-private partnerships approaches for climate adaptation. 
Conduct quantitative research and business analysis for new opportunities in the climate adaptation and financing market, and identify relevant use cases for the applications of One Concern resilience platform of those markets. 
