Create customer-ready materials to successfully position One Concern solutions to the customers. 
 Requirements 
At least five (5) years of relevant experience in the climate risk adaptation, climate resilience Investment and risk financing domains. Experience of working for/with (re)insurance companies or brokers, asset managers, or climate finance companies will be a big plus 
Demonstrated experience of working on climate adaptation approaches and risk financing options (through enterprise risk management budget, bank loans, blended finance, resilience bonds, or insurance) 
Good understanding of the (re)insurance/financial sector, climate risk and climate finance industry, and private sector/public-private partnerships approaches for climate adaptation 
MS or Ph.D degree in Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Actuarial Science, Statistics Engineering, or a related technical field 
Demonstrated experience of working on new solutions working with customers and teams in a multidisciplinary environment 
Strong communication, quantitative and analytical skills 
Creative, innovative mindset for identifying and solving open-ended problems 
High willingness and flexibility to travel (domestic/international) - potentially >25% travel under normal, post COVID-19 conditions 
